Yo, doing some research around unenrolling a contact from a sequence when a meeting is booked per <https://knowledge.HubSpot.com/sequences/unenroll-from-sequence|this knowledge base article>
We are utilizing <https://legacydocs.HubSpot.com/docs/methods/engagements/create_engagement|POST /engagements/v1/engagements> when creating a meeting with a request like
```{
    engagement: {
      active: true,
      type: 'MEETING',
      ownerId: some_owner_id,
      timestamp: start_time
    }.compact,
    associations: {
      contactIds: some_contact_id,
      companyIds: [],
      dealIds: [],
      ownerIds: []
    },
    metadata: {
      title: some_title,
      body: some_body,
      startTime: start_time,
      endTime: end_time
    }
}```
Our understanding is that when this engagement “meeting” is created it should unenroll the contact from any sequence they were added to but are finding that this is not happening via the api calls. Any insight?
